--- PART 3: SIGN AT EACH RESONANCE LEVEL ---
For q-resonant pair (a,b) with qa=b: sign(D^{2n}) vs chi(ab)
chi(ab) = chi(qa^2) = chi(q)*chi(a)^2 = chi(q)
For qa=-b: chi(ab) = chi(-qa^2) = chi(-q)

  p=7 (3 mod 4):
    chi(3)=-1, chi(5)=-1, chi(7)=+0
    chi(-3)=+1, chi(-5)=+1, chi(-7)=+0

